author: cbs8
title: 2 found stabbed to death in Baton Rouge house
text:
BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) - Police in Baton Rouge are investigating the stabbing deaths of two people in a house in the city.
Cpl. Don Coppola says police responded to a call about the stabbings Saturday morning around 7:45.
The dead were identified as 46-year-old Johnson Armstrong III, who lived at the house; and 45-year-old Corey Steptore of Gonzales.
Police were seeking information a possible motive and suspects.
